
Overview of noun buckle

The noun buckle has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (2) buckle -- (fastener that fastens together two ends of a belt or strap; often has loose prong)
2. warp, buckle -- (a shape distorted by twisting or folding)

Overview of verb buckle

The verb buckle has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (1) buckle, clasp -- (fasten with a buckle or buckles)
2. (1) buckle, crumple -- (fold or collapse; "His knees buckled")
3. (1) heave, buckle, warp -- (bend out of shape, as under pressure or from heat; "The highway buckled during the heat wave")
